example: they showed no eagerness to spread the gospel
they disliked his zeal in demonstrating his superiority
he tried to explain his forwardness in battle

tr: a positive feeling of wanting to push ahead with something

value.def: If you are eager to do or have something, you want to do or have it very much.

example.ex: Robert was eager to talk about life in the Army...
example.tran: 罗伯特很想谈谈陆军生活。

example.ex: When my own son was five years old, I became eager for another baby...
example.tran: 我家儿子5岁的时候，我特别想再要一个孩子。

example.ex: The low prices still pull in crowds of eager buyers.
example.tran: 低廉的价格仍然吸引了大批热切的买家。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, ADJ to-inf, ADJ <l>for</l> n

value.def: If you look or sound eager, you look or sound as if you expect something interesting or enjoyable to happen.

example.ex: Arty sneered at the crowd of eager faces around him...
example.tran: 阿蒂对他身边那些期盼的面孔嗤之以鼻。

example.ex: Her voice was girlish and eager.
example.tran: 她的声音像个小姑娘似的，而且带着一股急不可耐。

value.tran: （看起来或听上去）急切的，期盼的

example.ex: 'So what do you think will happen?' he asked eagerly.
example.tran: “那么你觉得会发生什么？”他急切地问道。
说话急切、上气不接下气的女人
